RODIMUS PRIMAL nodded as he listened to PERCEPTOR. "Well let's go see
what's going on down here."

He led PERCEPTOR down a long straight tunnel, one that looked to have
been dug a long time ago. As they approached the bottom the radiation
levels began to climb. "I hope thee are no protohumans down here."
RODIMUS said quietly as he came to a stop. "These radiation levels
would be lethal to them."

They came to a corner and RODIMUS glanced around carefully and down
the tunnel it opened into a large chamber, one that looked much newer
in construction and there were protohumans, digging in the dirt with
shovels.

There were other figures standing over them but there were larger and
bulkier as if they were wearing some sort of protective gear.

"Work!" One of the bulkier figures said to the protohumans.

The protohumans looked like they were sick and weak.
